The paper focuses on the security analysis of smart contracts, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the programming languages and toolchains used for smart contracts, which relates to software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL). The use of logic specifications and semantic logic relations in the analysis pipeline suggests a connection to logic in computer science (cs.LO). Finally, the paper discusses the efficiency and scalability of the framework, which relates to distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
